"Arthur" faces out to the west and a touch south, ushering in the sun via its two story window set. An iron picket and oak staircase leads down to the cellar. An outstanding feature is the third floor family room and secondary master - plus the best laundry room view around. The basements been roughed in for second laundry and bath. The main floor powder room is tucked away by the garage entry. Kitchen-Aided dovetail drawers compliment the quartz capped install. Sliders and a transome provide the dining space with extra flair for a nice meal, while the millwork in the family room sets the scene for basking under a two story window set (or for basking in the firelight in winter). Juliette can look down from either an indoor or outdoor balcony, and the secondary master has an office/guest room with spa written all over it. The two kids bedrooms will have to fight over being the last one to step foot on the fun tile in the main bath. Calculate the price of downtown real estate, and discover the value in this over-2,800 SqFt custom build. All we did was stage it with a clock, as you'll know when its your time. (52519557)

The second fraternal Brickworks twin in Downtown Kitchener, steps from the LRT, Expressway and Centre in the Square, on what used to be Kaiser Street. The name of the street may have changed after the war, but the resilient people that built the community stayed. Hard work still pays off in this area of diversified economic activity, and we know to do our best and be happy in this German town, as anything less than 10 out of 10 is a "nein". Thats the spirit that got us here - good to see it come back to Berlin. 101 Mansion was built of European brick to proudly stand the test of time. Inside, youll feel the spirits close, whether it be from heavenly beams of light from the 2.5 story cathedral ceilings that span from the loft to family room, down to the greeted guests in the elevated front foyer... or in your cozy, yet vast gathering space, as you raise a toast with your feet to the fire. Down the upstairs hall, past the delightful vaulted family room, is the master with spa-like en-suite to warm up your soles in the AM, and walk through closet access for some schnapps and reflection in the PM. Past the convenient laundry are two equal-sized bedrooms separated by a wall, sharing the main bath. The French doored loft can be used as a bedroom, studio or office, or all of the above, with its own stunning bath. Instantly irreplaceable, this is Real Estate to an old world standard, taking into account modern day expectations. Welcome to this Kaiser of a Mansion in old Berlin. (52540850)
